%I A397192 #18 Jun 19 2026 12:25:48
%S A397192 589
%N A397192 Least m such that n = 1/s_1 + 1/s_2 + ... + 1/s_k with 1 < s_1 < s_2 < ... < s_k = m and s_1, ..., s_k are all semiprime.
%C A397192 Li proves that a(n) exists for each n.
%H A397192 David A. Corneth, <a href="/A397192/a397192.png">Solution for n = 1</a>
%H A397192 Shisheng Li, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.15159">Every natural number is a sum of distinct semiprime unit fractions</a>, arXiv preprint (2026). arXiv:2606.15159 [math.NT]
%F A397192 Trivial lower bound: log log a(n) >> sqrt(n).
%e A397192 1 = 1/6 + 1/10 + 1/14 + 1/15 + 1/21 + 1/22 + 1/26 + 1/33 + 1/34 + 1/35 + 1/38 + 1/39 + 1/46 + 1/51 + 1/55 + 1/57 + 1/62 + 1/65 + 1/69 + 1/77 + 1/82 + 1/85 + 1/87 + 1/91 + 1/93 + 1/95 + 1/106 + 1/115 + 1/118 + 1/119 + 1/123 + 1/129 + 1/145 + 1/159 + 1/203 + 1/217 + 1/221 + 1/247 + 1/265 + 1/287 + 1/295 + 1/299 + 1/319 + 1/341 + 1/377 + 1/391 + 1/403 + 1/413 + 1/473 + 1/559 + 1/583 + 1/589.
